===Noun===
'''proposition''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''propositions''')

#(''uncountable'') The act of offering (an idea) for [[consideration]].
#(''countable'') An idea or a plan offered.
#(''in business settings'') (''countable'') The [[terms]] of a [[transaction]] offered.
#{{logic}} (''countable'') The content of an [[assertion]] that may be taken as being true or false and is considered abstractly without reference to the linguistic sentence that constitutes the assertion.
#In some states of the [[US]], a proposed [[statute]] or [[constitutional amendment]] to be voted on by the [[electorate]].

